pr_body:
#### Short description of what this resolves:

With this pull request, login functionality will start working in the deploy cli tool.

#### How it works:

1) If you are currently in your project folder which you wanna deploy, type

```js
$ metacall-deploy
```

2) With a different name for your project

```js
$ metacall-deploy --projectName=differentName
```

3) If you are in some other directory and still wanna deploy a project which is at some other path,

```js
$ metacall-deploy --workdir=absolutePathToTheProject
```

- [x] My branch is up-to-date with the Upstream `master` branch.

Video demonstration - https://asciinema.org/a/LPNhsQaT5OUX9TUcZ8z5s4cxP

**Description**
Added help command.

**Context**
Printing CLI guide needs to be updated more than this, but for now it's OK to make it work.

#### Short description of what this resolves:

With this pull request, you can look at all of your deployments on FAAS.

#### How it works:

1) Open your terminal & hit the command given below:-

```js
$ metacall-deploy  --inspect
```

#### Screenshots

![WhatsApp Image 2022-02-18 at 10 11 13 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/65965202/154729313-3c86359f-832e-485e-83e8-c3dcd122a202.jpeg)

![WhatsApp Image 2022-02-18 at 10 11 50 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/65965202/154729321-e882ec66-0e0c-4be4-b6a7-c8d065b55937.jpeg)


- [x] My branch is up-to-date with the Upstream `master` branch.

### Description
This pr adds the feature to delete your deploys.

### Additional Context
We could have added the whole list logic inside the delete.ts file, but in the future, I will be working on the --force flag, and that too will require the delete component, that's why made it reusable.

### How does it work?

```CPP

Step 1) Hit the below command:- 

$ metacall-deploy --delete

Step 2) It will provide the list of available deployments.

Step 3) Select one of the deployments and done.
```

### Checklist
- [x] My branch is up to date with the upstream master branch.
